{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774532223,"nonce":"RxIBIU4rn+q9pfJ15U4LmxCs6BE=","message":"**Minimax adversarial training diagnostic — SISU velocity puzzle**\n\n## Experimental Setup\n\n- Architecture: minimax adversarial training with single GaussianBumpAdversary (3 Gaussian bumps)\n- Hyperparameters: force_max=2.0, n_adversary_steps=5, batch_size=250, controller_lr=1e-4, adversary_lr=3e-4\n- Task: center-out delayed reaches, constant length 0.5, all from origin\n- Training: 2000 warmup batches + 5000 adversarial batches; evaluated at batch 1499 checkpoint\n- Replication: 4 independent seeds (separate processes, not vmapped replicates)\n\n## SISU Velocity Results (pert_scale=0)\n\nAll seeds show zero SISU velocity effect at batch 1499:\n\n- Seed 0: vel(S=0)=0.6983, vel(S=1)=0.6983, Δvel=0.00%\n- Seed 1: vel(S=0)=0.6397, vel(S=1)=0.6397, Δvel=0.00%\n- Seed 2: vel(S=0)=0.6608, vel(S=1)=0.6608, Δvel=0.00%\n- Seed 3: vel(S=0)=0.7289, vel(S=1)=0.7289, Δvel=0.00%\n\n## Adversary Convergence (batch 1499, all seeds)\n\n- Force norms: 10.8 (init) → 22.7 (2.1× growth)\n- Peak forces saturate at force_max=2.0 clipping\n- Bump widths: 0.6–1.1s on 1.3s trial = broad/flat forces, not localized\n- Seed 3 anomaly: 2/3 bumps placed at negative time (before trial); adversary partially collapsed\n- Interpretation: adversary learned \"push hard everywhere\" rather than a structured temporal strategy\n\n## Loss Dynamics\n\nctrl_loss ≈ adv_loss across all batches (max diff 0.01):\n\n- Seed 0: early=9.02 → late=7.78 (gradual decrease; controller winning)\n- Seed 1: early=8.81 → late=8.01 (gradual decrease)\n- Seed 2: early=9.76 → late=10.81 (INCREASE; adversary spike at batch 1000 to 14.8 — unstable)\n- Seed 3: early=9.99 → late=5.11 (rapid decrease; adversary collapsed)\n\n## Conclusion\n\nMinimax training with a single GaussianBumpAdversary does not produce the SISU velocity effect by batch 1499 (~30% of training budget). The adversary converges to broad constant forces saturating force_max, and the controller adapts without exploiting SISU information. Training was stopped early based on this diagnostic.","files":null}]}